tten by the leading authors in the field and fully updated since the Health and Social Care Act 2012, the book is also fully evidence- and research-based, while still being accessible and applicable to everyday practice. Aimed at students, practitioners, managers and policy makers in health and social care, and including new reflective exercises and boxed examples, this is still the one book that everyone in the field should read.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aInteragency coordinationzGreat Britain. 0aMedical policyzGreat Britain. 0aPublic healthzGreat Britain. 0aPublic welfarezGreat Britain. 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh1 aDickinson, Helen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783111196343oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144731281940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447318743423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447318743/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2014